summary: Multiple international health organizations, including the World Health Organization (WHO), have declared the ongoing mpox (formerly known as monkeypox) outbreaks as a public health emergency of international concern. name: Booktopia
summary: Australia's leading online bookstore, Booktopia, has been acquired by digiDirect, an online electronics retailer. The sale secures the future of Booktopia and its hundreds of jobs. The new owner plans to invest millions in the business and revitalize its operations. The purchase follows a period of financial difficulties for Booktopia, which led it to suspend trading. However, shareholders have lost out as a result of the sale. Despite this, the successful acquisition is a positive outcome for Booktopia and its customers, ensuring the continued availability of a wide range of books in Australia.

An analysis of the game focused on Manchester City's dominance, while an article discussed the challenges faced by Pep Guardiola in his ninth season at the club. Manchester City unveiled an interactive fan experience called 'Man City Virtual Etihad Stadium' in collaboration with Sony. Sky Sports provided a match report and highlights, while CNET offered instructions on how to livestream the match from various locations. Amidst ongoing legal proceedings, the Premier League chief urged the resolution of Manchester City's 115 charges, raising the possibility of relegation. The Guardian reported on the goals scored by Haaland and Kovacic that contributed to Manchester City's victory.

name: John Aprea
summary: John Aprea, a renowned actor known for his roles in "The Godfather Part II" and "Full House," has passed away at the age of 83. Aprea's remarkable career spanned decades, leaving an unforgettable mark on both the big screen and television. His portrayal of Don Altobello in "The Godfather Part II" and Uncle Jesse's grumpy brother-in-law, Joey Gladstone, in "Full House" cemented his status as a beloved character actor. Aprea's passing has been met with sadness and tributes from the entertainment industry and fans alike, honoring his contributions to the world of cinema and television.

name: Shai Bolton
summary: Richmond Tigers' star forward Shai Bolton has reportedly requested a trade back to his home state of Western Australia. The news follows rumors of an exodus from the Tigers, with Dustin Martin announcing his retirement and Jack Riewoldt retiring as well. Bolton's departure would be a significant blow to Richmond, who signed him to a six-year, $6 million contract in 2021. However, some believe it could be a good move for the Tigers, allowing them to rebuild their team and potentially secure a higher draft pick in the trade. Bolton's manager has since denied the reports, saying that the player is happy at Richmond and has no intention of leaving.

Despite his absence from the squad for the Crystal Palace match, manager Thomas Frank has denied that a departure is imminent. However, multiple outlets have reported interest from Arsenal, Chelsea, Tottenham, and Al Ahli in Saudi Arabia. Frank has expressed his hope that a transfer will be resolved soon, while Yahoo Sports claims Arsenal has decided against signing Toney.
